						               													<description>MAKTA a.k.a Last hit is a board game in a fantasy world where the player with the highest honor score wins when peace comes to the village by defeating monsters, collecting items, and completing quests.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;MAKTA is a turn-based board game for 2 to 5 players.&amp;#10;When it's their turn, players must collect honor points by moving around the map, performing events, or using skill cards to disrupt and subdue enemies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A total of 5 characters, warrior, archer, wizard, king, and farmer, have different stats and unique skill cards. Players can choose and play according to their own preferences.&amp;#10;There are various types of skills such as skills that increase strength during battle or attack enemies located at a distance, and each character has 5 unique skills.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The map is made by randomly arranging 36 map tiles, and consists of 7 types of buildings, 3 types of resource facilities, 4 types of events, 12 types of monsters, and 10 types of quests.&amp;#10;Items are equipment that help you fight. You can only put one item in the inventory slot of the information board, and you cannot have more than one item from the same part.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
